UNDIAGNOSED DEATHS, POULTRY - PHILIPPINES: (COTABATO) REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
*****************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 13 Feb 2020
Source: MindaNews [abridged, edited]
https://www.mindanews.com/top-stories/2020/02/unknown-disease-hits-fighting-cocks-in-cotabato-city/


An unknown disease has killed several fighting cocks in Barangay Rosary Heights 1 [Cotabato City] in the past few days.

Among those killed by the disease were 5 cocks at Mangga Boys game farm. The animals all died inside their cages and showed symptoms like swollen head, blindness and severe flu.

[RC], one of the gamefowl owners, said the chickens had colds and fever, and became weak.

"We noticed that the unknown disease has led to death of fighting cocks starting last week. We attempted to treat with antibiotics and other medicines, but it didn't work," a caretaker in one game farm said.

Owners burned the dead chickens before burying them, a measure which they hoped would stop the unknown disease from spreading. But city veterinarian Dr. Robert Malcontento said cases of avian diseases should be reported to his office. He said laboratory tests are needed to know the diseases that killed the animals.

[Byline: Ferdinandh B. Cabrera]

